data.text:
@biochemistries @guardian Everyone wearing something 80% effective is a massive infection control due to the network effect. The gains from switching to 95% effective are marginal.

All it takes is for another province-wide outbreak in China like in Hubei and the PPE supply chain will collapse again.

data.text: @guardian Really wish @guardian would think twice before big headlines like this, which may make people abandon woven masks. Woven masks are still great: blocking over 80% of the risk. Meanwhile, non-woven masks are a big litter problem and needed for the global medical supply chain.
